---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Accessibility Statement | Town of Littleton, NH" description="The Town of Littleton is committed to ensuring digital accessibility for people with disabilities.">

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section aria-labelledby="hero-heading" class="bg-light-blue py-16 text-center">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-8">
      <h2 id="hero-heading" class="text-4xl font-bold text-navy mb-4">Accessibility Statement</h2>
      <p class="text-xl text-body-text max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        The Town of Littleton is committed to ensuring digital accessibility for people with disabilities.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Commitment -->
  <section aria-labelledby="commitment-heading" class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-8">
      <h2 id="commitment-heading" class="text-3xl font-bold text-navy mb-6 text-center">Our Commitment</h2>
      <p class="text-body-text mb-4 leading-relaxed">
        The Town of Littleton is dedicated to providing a website that is accessible to the widest possible audience,
        regardless of technology or ability. We are actively working to increase the accessibility and usability of
        our website and strive to conform to the Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.1 Level AA standards.
      </p>
      <p class="text-body-text leading-relaxed">
        Our ongoing accessibility efforts include ensuring keyboard navigation throughout the site, compatibility
        with screen readers such as JAWS, NVDA, and VoiceOver, sufficient color contrast ratios for all text and
        interactive elements, and descriptive alternative text for all meaningful images. We regularly review and
        test our website to identify and address any accessibility barriers.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Standards -->
  <section aria-labelledby="standards-heading" class="py-16 bg-light-blue">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-8">
      <h2 id="standards-heading" class="text-3xl font-bold text-navy mb-8 text-center">Accessibility Standards</h2>
      <div class="standards-grid">
        <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border-t-4 border-gold">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-navy mb-3">WCAG 2.1 Level AA</h3>
          <p class="text-body-text leading-relaxed">
            We strive to meet the Web Content Accessibility Guidelines 2.1 Level AA standards, which address
            the major barriers that affect users with visual, auditory, physical, speech, cognitive, and
            neurological disabilities.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border-t-4 border-gold">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-navy mb-3">Keyboard Accessible</h3>
          <p class="text-body-text leading-relaxed">
            All functionality on our website is available using only a keyboard. Users can navigate through
            links, buttons, and form fields using Tab, Enter, and arrow keys without requiring a mouse.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border-t-4 border-gold">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-navy mb-3">Screen Reader Compatible</h3>
          <p class="text-body-text leading-relaxed">
            Our website has been tested with common screen readers including JAWS, NVDA, and VoiceOver.
            We use proper heading structure, ARIA labels, and semantic HTML to ensure content is announced correctly.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Known Limitations -->
  <section aria-labelledby="limitations-heading" class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-8">
      <h2 id="limitations-heading" class="text-3xl font-bold text-navy mb-6 text-center">Known Limitations</h2>
      <p class="text-body-text mb-4 leading-relaxed">
        While we strive to ensure accessibility across all pages, some older PDF documents on our website
        may not be fully accessible to screen readers. These documents were created before our current
        accessibility standards were implemented.
      </p>
      <p class="text-body-text mb-4 leading-relaxed">
        We are committed to remediating these documents upon request. If you need an accessible version of
        any document, please contact us and we will provide an alternative format within a reasonable timeframe.
      </p>
      <p class="text-body-text leading-relaxed">
        Additionally, some third-party content embedded on our site, such as external maps or social media
        feeds, may not meet our accessibility standards. We work with our vendors to encourage accessibility
        improvements and provide alternative ways to access this information when possible.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Feedback -->
  <section aria-labelledby="feedback-heading" class="py-16 bg-light-blue">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-8 text-center">
      <h2 id="feedback-heading" class="text-3xl font-bold text-navy mb-6">Accessibility Feedback</h2>
      <p class="text-body-text mb-8 max-w-2xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
        We welcome your feedback on the accessibility of the Town of Littleton website. If you encounter
        any accessibility barriers or have suggestions for improvement, please let us know.
      </p>
      <div class="feedback-card">
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div>
            <span class="font-semibold text-navy">Email: </span>
            <a
              href="mailto:accessibility@littletonnh.gov"
              class="text-navy underline hover:no-underline focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-gold focus:ring-offset-2 rounded"
            >
              accessibility@littletonnh.gov
            </a>
          </div>
          <div>
            <span class="font-semibold text-navy">Phone: </span>
            <a
              href="tel:+16035550100"
              class="text-navy underline hover:no-underline focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-gold focus:ring-offset-2 rounded"
              aria-label="Call (603) 555-0100"
            >
              (603) 555-0100
            </a>
          </div>
          <div class="text-body-text">
            <span class="font-semibold text-navy">Response Time: </span>
            We aim to respond within 2 business days
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <a
        href="/contact"
        class="inline-block bg-navy text-white px-8 py-3 rounded font-semibold hover:opacity-90 focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-navy focus:ring-offset-2 mt-8"
      >
        Contact Us
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Technical Info -->
  <section aria-labelledby="technical-heading" class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-8">
      <h2 id="technical-heading" class="text-3xl font-bold text-navy mb-6 text-center">Technical Specifications</h2>
      <p class="text-body-text mb-4 leading-relaxed">This website is built using the following technologies:</p>
      <ul class="tech-list">
        <li>HTML5</li>
        <li>CSS3 / Tailwind CSS v4</li>
        <li>Astro framework</li>
        <li>WAI-ARIA attributes for enhanced accessibility</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-body-text mb-4 leading-relaxed">The website has been tested on the following browsers:</p>
      <ul class="tech-list">
        <li>Google Chrome (latest version)</li>
        <li>Mozilla Firefox (latest version)</li>
        <li>Apple Safari (latest version)</li>
        <li>Microsoft Edge (latest version)</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-body-text mt-6">
        <span class="font-semibold text-navy">Last Reviewed:</span> October 2025
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .standards-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 24px;
    max-width: 1000px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .standards-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }

  .feedback-card {
    background: white;
    padding: 32px;
    border-radius: 8px;
    max-width: 420px;
    margin: 0 auto 32px;
    text-align: left;
  }

  .tech-list {
    list-style: disc;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    color: #1E2D3D;
  }
  .tech-list li {
    margin-bottom: 8px;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
</style>